metadata.title: Groundfish Catch and Effort Database (Canada)

creators.name: Oceans Canada, Science Branch - Data Analyst

metadata.description:
Parameter
Groundfish catch and effort data for  trawl, sablefish trap and longline gear types

The catch and effort data were obtained from daily logbooks filled out by fishers.  Information recorded and stored in the database include area and depth of capture, amount of effort expended, species caught and amounts. Includes trawl, sablefish trap and longline fisheries

Geographic Area
Pacific coast of Canada

Publication
Annual Reports, CDFO Technical Reports

Other Comments
"Trawl catch and effort data is available from 1954-1995.  Information for trap is available from 1979-1995 and longline information is available from 1979-1985.  
Collection of catch and effort data is continuing but data will be housed in a new 
relational database that is in its final phases of development.
Throughout the years the GFCATCH database has evolved and most changes have only been documented internally.  Please contact the custodian for more details on the database."

[ A TCODE project ]
